Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.27,0:00:05.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm begging you! Please reinvestigate my sister's suicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.65,0:00:08.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, now, don't get so agitated.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.02,0:00:10.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, would you tell us your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.36,0:00:11.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.69,0:00:15.03,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,My name's Misaki Yanai.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.39,0:05:20.60,Signs,,0,0,0,,Nagisa Yanai (22)\NMisaki's Sister
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.50,0:04:24.38,Signs,,0,0,0,,Harue Kodama (25)\NTheatre Club Advisor
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.03,0:00:18.58,Signs,,0,0,0,,Misaki Yanai (17)\NYanai Seibi Educational Institute, 2nd Year Student
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.03,0:00:19.33,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I went to the same school as Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Sonoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} until the end of middle school.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.33,0:00:25.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the start of high school, she transferred to the Yanai Seibi Educational Institute, where her mum's the director.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.50,0:00:28.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, the famous Yanai Seibi Educational Institute?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.92,0:00:31.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, you said you have doubts about your sister's suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.88,0:00:34.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, Nagisa would...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.34,0:00:37.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My sister would {\i1}never{\i0} have committed suicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.39,0:00:42.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if the police are calling it a suicide, then they must have some evidence...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.73,0:00:44.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There were two witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.77,0:00:47.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, there were witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.15,0:00:50.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I was one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.94,0:00:52.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.90,0:00:56.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But something's got to be wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.41,0:00:57.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.78,0:00:59.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I beg you!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.33,0:01:02.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please, prove that my sister didn't commit suicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.25,0:01:05.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That isn't going to be easy, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.77,0:01:13.15,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10\c&HAAAA00\t(0,4370,\c)}Seeking comprehensive answers,\Nhe solves every mystery and code!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.15,0:01:17.70,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10\t(0,1750,\c&H88AA00)}The client's a female student, the stage is a school campus, and the truth is astonishing!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.70,0:01:19.37,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10\c&H88AA00)\t(0,1670,\c)}He sees the single truth for what it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.37,0:01:21.45,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10\t(0,2070,\c&HAA00AA)}and looks like a kid but has the mind of an adult!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.45,0:01:23.62,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10\c&HAA00AA\t(0,1870,\c&H0000FF)}His name? Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.47,0:03:13.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, even the forensics confirmed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.48,0:03:17.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no doubt, Nagisa Yanai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} committed suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.02,0:03:20.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As I thought. Thank you, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.99,0:03:25.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, Inspector Megure confirmed it too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.49,0:03:27.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know that!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.53,0:03:30.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I came to see you, Detective Mouri.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.54,0:03:31.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Misaki...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.66,0:03:32.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sheesh!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.71,0:03:34.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, somebody help me out here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.67,0:03:37.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Uncle...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.00,0:03:40.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would you at least listen to her testimony?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.67,0:03:42.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,R-Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.38,0:03:47.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, calm down and just tell Uncle what you saw.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.05,0:03:48.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.85,0:03:50.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm only lending an ear, miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.27,0:03:56.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Five days ago, just before 6 PM,\Nas the evening was starting...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.85,0:03:59.57,Signs,,0,0,0,,Wet paint!!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.85,0:03:59.57,Signs,,0,0,0,,Wet paint!!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.85,0:04:01.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kodama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} asked me to come with her to a bench because she had to talk to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.69,0:04:03.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who's Kodama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.45,0:04:08.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's the advisor for both the high school and university theatre clubs.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.91,0:04:11.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My sister and I were both in the theatre club.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.83,0:04:18.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My sister was chosen to play the main character next year in a play for the institute's anniversary festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.84,0:04:24.38,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10\an8}The play's not going to take place until early\Nnext year, so the theme hasn't been decided yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.38,0:04:29.05,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That is to say, whether to make it a tragedy or a comedy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.05,0:04:31.39,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Yeah, my sister told me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.39,0:04:34.27,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The question is whether a happy ending would be better since it's an anniversary festival,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.27,0:04:37.35,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}or whether a lively performance that'd touch people's hearts would be better.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.35,0:04:39.90,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Right, Nagisa{\rHonorifics - Flashback\be10}-san{\r\be10} isn't sure either.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.90,0:04:43.61,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's why I wanted to find out your opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.03,0:04:45.65,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But she's late...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.65,0:04:48.57,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Nagisa{\rHonorifics - Flashback\be10}-san{\r\be10} told me to wait for her here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.32,0:04:53.24,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's the model club clubroom, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.24,0:04:55.62,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I thought the club members left already...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.62,0:04:58.42,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Perhaps it's their advisor, Shibagaki{\rHonorifics - Flashback\be10}-sensei{\r\be10}?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.42,0:05:03.00,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He should've been in a meeting with the director since 5:30 though...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.22,0:05:10.76,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Sis?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.76,0:05:13.26,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Why is Yanai{\rHonorifics - Flashback\be10}-san{\r\be10} there...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.77,0:05:16.06,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.06,0:05:17.10,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Sis!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.89,0:05:20.60,Signs,,34,0,0,,What did your sister\Nhang the rope from?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.60,0:05:23.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That room has its ceiling beams exposed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.61,0:05:25.78,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Sis! Sis!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.78,0:05:27.61,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's no use, that room's soundproofed!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.12,0:05:33.33,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.83,0:05:42.38,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's locked!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.38,0:05:43.84,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Why today, of all days?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.84,0:05:46.51,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}I know! Call the director's room!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.51,0:05:47.09,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.30,0:05:50.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was the director's room closer?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.68,0:05:56.68,Dialogue,,10,10,0,,Yeah. It'd be a lot faster than us going all the way round to the front entrance. Also, both rooms are on the 2nd floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.68,0:05:59.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's where your mother was, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.27,0:06:01.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah, and that Shibagaki teacher, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.86,0:06:06.78,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.15,0:06:09.86,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}What? What are you saying?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.86,0:06:11.86,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}My sister's in danger!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.86,0:06:15.16,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The model club clubroom! Hurry there!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.30,0:06:28.46,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Nagisa! Nagisa!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.84,0:06:31.18,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}How could you do this to me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.84,0:06:35.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was that Shibagaki teacher your sister's boyfriend?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.51,0:06:37.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was in charge of the institute's finances,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.72,0:06:41.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and they were planning to get married once she graduated...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.48,0:06:45.31,Signs,,0,0,0,,Tōichirō Shibagaki (26)\NNagisa's Fiancé
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.23,0:06:43.31,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10\an8}How could you leave me behind like this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.31,0:06:46.61,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10\an8}It can't be! I can't believe this!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.36,0:06:53.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Misaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.07,0:06:56.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you saw it with your own eyes, then what makes you think it's not suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.62,0:06:59.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There has to be a reason, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.20,0:07:01.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She had a boyfriend who promised to marry her.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.71,0:07:05.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She should've been as happy as can be, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.17,0:07:08.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Would someone enjoying life really commit suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.80,0:07:11.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was an problem with her boyfriend...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.59,0:07:14.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.01,0:07:18.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shibagaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} and Kodama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}\Nwent to the same university...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.51,0:07:21.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And they used to be together.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.10,0:07:23.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's the other witness, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.52,0:07:26.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?! So he could've been two-timing her?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.06,0:07:26.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.52,0:07:28.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And they both admitted it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.19,0:07:33.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As the police investigation progressed,\NShibagaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} had to reluctantly reveal his past...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.82,0:07:36.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what did Kodama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} say about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.95,0:07:38.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's up with that boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.91,0:07:42.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't mind him, he's just a precocious little brat.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.33,0:07:44.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But sometimes, he's very perceptive.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.41,0:07:46.12,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}'Sometimes'?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.12,0:07:49.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, what did Kodama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} say?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.25,0:07:54.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She admitted she'd been with him in the past,\Nbut said she has nothing to do with him anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.26,0:07:56.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That sounds suspicious...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.80,0:07:59.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And they both work at the same school...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.39,0:08:04.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe Nagisa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} committed suicide because she was troubled about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.27,0:08:08.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no way she'd just quietly commit suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.52,0:08:14.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My sister would've done something like throw the engagement ring back at the cheating bastard.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.65,0:08:16.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.28,0:08:17.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something on your mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.86,0:08:22.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That scandal only came out with the police investigation, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.20,0:08:24.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did your sister know about it beforehand?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.71,0:08:26.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, you're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.50,0:08:28.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.00,0:08:32.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah, I was also looking after this for my sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.88,0:08:35.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See, it has 'Nagisa' engraved into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.88,0:08:39.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She asked me to go adjust its size at the store where it was bought.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.93,0:08:40.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.89,0:08:42.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The morning of the day she died.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.14,0:08:48.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then Nagisa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} didn't know about\Nwhat happened between the advisors yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.44,0:08:50.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And not just that...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.10,0:08:53.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She wanted it adjusted because she wanted to wear the bracelet forever, even after the wedding.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.40,0:08:56.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your sister sounds like she was so happy...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.15,0:09:00.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I just can't accept that she'd commit suicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.66,0:09:05.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you saw her do it with your own eyes...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.75,0:09:08.75,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}No!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.84,0:09:17.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The rope that was used was one the model club use when packaging models.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.51,0:09:23.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the stool she used to stand on rolled into a corner, behind a partition.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.43,0:09:30.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since the stool had casters, it probably rolled away from the jolt of her jumping off.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.94,0:09:35.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But this is pretty impressive. Is this a model of the Yanai Seibi Educational Institute?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.44,0:09:37.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Were all the models built by the students?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.40,0:09:41.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The club members worked together to build them, but I'm sure their advisor helped too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.45,0:09:43.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Shibagaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.70,0:09:47.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he's a fan of miniatures and a total war nerd.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.33,0:09:52.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He even contributed his entire collection for display there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.42,0:09:54.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Amazing...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.09,0:09:58.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a remote-control model of the Elefant, developed by the Germans during World War II!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.92,0:10:00.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You do know a lot, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.34,0:10:02.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.14,0:10:04.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You {\i1}are{\i0} a boy, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.35,0:10:08.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To girls, {\i1}this{\i0} is the kind of stuff that rings bells.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.02,0:10:12.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.65,0:10:14.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that okay, Takagi?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.06,0:10:17.86,Dialogue,,10,10,0,,If the Inspector scolds you for bringing these photos here,\NI'm not gonna take responsibility, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.86,0:10:20.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'll be fine, I brought them because it wasn't a case for the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.82,0:10:24.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But these kids here are trying to prove it wasn't a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.95,0:10:26.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.99,0:10:28.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't go 'I see' on me!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.66,0:10:29.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Listen up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.71,0:10:31.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know what's weird about this case?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.42,0:10:34.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's what the benefit from the victim's death was...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.79,0:10:39.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since in this case, everybody ended up losing out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.46,0:10:43.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kodama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Shibagaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} were widely suspected of being involved in a scandal.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.01,0:10:47.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Director Yanai, in shock from the loss of her daughter, declared she'd close down the campus.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.97,0:10:51.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if there {\i1}was{\i0} a killer, nobody would benefit from this!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.18,0:10:53.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no motive behind this crime!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.77,0:10:56.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.69,0:10:58.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did something catch your eye?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.40,0:11:04.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, it's hard to tell what it's like with just photos, so why don't we go to the scene!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.53,0:11:06.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To the scene?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.70,0:11:10.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah! We might find something if we take a look around, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.66,0:11:13.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You don't mind, right, Detective Takagi?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.08,0:11:18.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's not sealed off or anything, so you should be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.00,0:11:19.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not going.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.46,0:11:23.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you everything later then, Uncle.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.30,0:11:34.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It should be about time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.01,0:11:35.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, there she is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.68,0:11:42.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez! Act serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.02,0:11:44.19,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Oh, geez. Guess she'll never{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10} chan{\r\be10}ge.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.36,0:11:47.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.36,0:11:51.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When my sister was there, I could see her whole face.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.65,0:11:53.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll go and tell her then.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.53,0:11:55.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll call you when I get there!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.07,0:11:56.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.58,0:12:02.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The back door was locked then, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.54,0:12:03.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.25,0:12:07.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Does this far look about right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.92,0:12:11.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that should do. Try getting on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.59,0:12:15.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about now?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.97,0:12:18.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it looks perfect now!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.85,0:12:20.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.49,0:12:38.57,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Crawler tracks? Looks like it crashed pretty hard into the furniture...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.29,0:12:44.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.21,0:12:47.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can we call this reproduction done?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.71,0:12:48.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.58,0:12:49.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then—
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.97,0:12:59.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-You okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.85,0:13:02.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you're worried about me, then hurry up and get off me...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.56,0:13:04.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.18,0:13:07.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hello, Mouri Detective Agency.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.56,0:13:09.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Misaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.44,0:13:14.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for the case, the detective agency's\Nstatement remains the same as yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.11,0:13:16.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'm aware.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.32,0:13:23.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, my mother and I still can't put our minds at ease unless you come to the scene and explain it to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.62,0:13:25.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you already know what happened...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.87,0:13:29.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please, all I want is an explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.59,0:13:32.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.92,0:13:34.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.55,0:13:37.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But all I'll give is an explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.09,0:13:39.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes! Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.63,0:13:41.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See you later, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.01,0:13:47.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, if it'll help her accept her sister's actions, I have no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.14,0:13:50.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess it's just another part of being a Great Detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.98,0:13:54.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What on Earth is Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} starting up now?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.32,0:13:56.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He really didn't tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.07,0:13:59.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, he just insisted that we'd understand if we came here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.57,0:14:05.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bear in mind that due to the school closing down, we don't have much time to spare.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.08,0:14:07.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, sorry to keep you waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.71,0:14:12.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's the Inspector doing here too—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.59,0:14:19.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.51,0:14:24.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He went straight into Sleeping Kogorō mode!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.01,0:14:27.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry to keep you waiting, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.18,0:14:30.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have come here at Misaki Yanai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s request, and—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.60,0:14:33.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That case is already closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.10,0:14:36.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm aware, as you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.15,0:14:38.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim is believed to have committed suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.86,0:14:45.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, on the same day, she'd asked her sister to get her bracelet resized.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.49,0:14:48.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doesn't that seem strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.37,0:14:52.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I believe I can answer that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.12,0:14:55.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She probably acted upon the spur of the moment when she found out about my actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.88,0:14:57.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.25,0:15:01.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, when and how did she find out about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.93,0:15:04.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, after she died it all—{ came out}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.89,0:15:07.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. So she had no way of knowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.43,0:15:14.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way, Misaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Ran and the others checked over the case yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.02,0:15:17.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, could you please repeat that reproduction?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.53,0:15:20.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Again?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.19,0:15:25.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I apologise, Yanai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}, but please just be patient.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.03,0:15:34.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} began by placing a step over there, but standing there didn't match the witnessed Nagisa's silhouette.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.08,0:15:38.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She had to move further from the window to achieve a perfect match.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.42,0:15:41.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Umm... It was about here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.97,0:15:43.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.72,0:15:45.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's nothing wrong or {\i1}right{\i0} with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.72,0:15:48.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would have been impossible\Nfor her to commit suicide there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.85,0:15:56.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As on that day, that spot happened to be occupied by a model of the Seibi Institute.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.02,0:16:01.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just to check, can you tell us, Misaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.44,0:16:04.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How much of the room was taken up by the model?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.53,0:16:07.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, uh... Up to this line.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.91,0:16:12.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As you can see, it would be impossible for her to stand there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.20,0:16:15.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, if she avoided the model and stood elsewhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.46,0:16:18.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,her position doesn't match with the witnesses' testimony.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.29,0:16:22.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To achieve the same perspective from a position closer to the window,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.51,0:16:25.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,a shorter step would need to be used.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.05,0:16:29.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on, the only thing here that looked like it could've been used was the stool.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.27,0:16:31.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, there was something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.64,0:16:33.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Inspector...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.48,0:16:36.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would she focus so much on where to commit suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.77,0:16:39.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's almost like she was taking up a position upon a stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.69,0:16:42.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it, back then, my sister...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.69,0:16:46.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I could see her face up to her waist,\Nas if it was all perfectly measured...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.32,0:16:48.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder if that was a coincidence?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.45,0:16:50.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What if it {\i1}wasn't{\i0} a coincidence?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.24,0:16:56.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What if someone had given her directions...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.12,0:16:59.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so that she'd be perfectly visible\Nto both of you in the garden.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.79,0:17:04.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're saying my sister wanted us to see her commit suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.51,0:17:10.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Correct. Nagisa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} wanted Kodama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} to see a 'suicide act'.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.76,0:17:14.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was why she deliberately chose the best position.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.02,0:17:18.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh! That's why she told me to\Nwait on that garden bench that day...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.35,0:17:21.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My sister's suicide was an act...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.69,0:17:23.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What Nagisa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} thought was this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.82,0:17:28.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She wanted the audience at the\Nanniversary festival to see her perform.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.24,0:17:31.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For that, she had to convince Kodama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} with her acting.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.24,0:17:37.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That way, even a tragic play could have been chosen for the festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.25,0:17:39.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It {\i1}does{\i0} make sense...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.71,0:17:43.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nagisa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} just could've done something like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.04,0:17:48.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She decided on her plan because someone eloquently convinced her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.72,0:17:51.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the only one who could do that...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.35,0:17:54.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! What are you trying to say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.01,0:17:58.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nothing. I never mentioned your name.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.52,0:18:03.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are many benches in the back garden,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.90,0:18:10.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but for some reason, every bench except the one Misaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} sat on had just been painted.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.03,0:18:17.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was told by the school staff that Shibayaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} requested that all the other benches be painted that specific day.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.45,0:18:22.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so, the premium seats for the play were prepared.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.04,0:18:29.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, on that day alone, the back door had been locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.18,0:18:33.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the one in charge of the keys was...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.22,0:18:36.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was you, Shibagaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.56,0:18:39.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.14,0:18:44.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if her suicide was meant to be only an act, how did it turn into the real thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.27,0:18:47.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That is because her step moved from underneath her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.73,0:18:48.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.82,0:18:51.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As a step, the stool was too tall.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.70,0:18:55.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the killer asked her to stand on a{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} tan{\r}k.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.58,0:18:56.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} tan{\r}k?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.74,0:19:00.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Elefant that was at the scene?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.25,0:19:03.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Takagi, would you bring it over here?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.29,0:19:08.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Most likely, it's a German cast alloy model.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.76,0:19:12.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which should handle a girl's weight easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.76,0:19:17.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you're saying she used this{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} tan{\r}k instead of the stool?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.38,0:19:52.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,6 PM — That was the time the victim had been told to begin her performance.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.01,0:19:59.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If someone used a remote control at that exact moment,\Nthen they could move the{\rHonorifics - Dialogue} tan{\r}k even from outside the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.85,0:20:04.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shibagaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}, you were using the\Ncalculator with your left hand at the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.94,0:20:07.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but you didn't take your right hand out of your pocket!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.48,0:20:11.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If there happened to be a remote control in that pocket...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.49,0:20:13.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's a false accusation!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.82,0:20:18.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was horrified when I got Misaki's call about Nagisa's suicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.12,0:20:19.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm a victim too!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.74,0:20:22.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're lying! All I told you was\Nto hurry to the model club clubroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.41,0:20:24.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't manage to say anything else!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.25,0:20:26.25,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}My sister's in danger!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.25,0:20:29.75,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The model club clubroom! Hurry there!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.75,0:20:32.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So how did you know she'd committed suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.63,0:20:35.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-That was just a figure of speech!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.22,0:20:39.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you arrived at the scene, was there any step here?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.22,0:20:43.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I could see the stool lying against the partition.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.00,0:20:44.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.18,0:20:49.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So when you went to help her, you confirmed that there was something she could've stood on.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.90,0:20:55.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's nonsense! When I donated my collection, I removed the motors from all the models!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.15,0:20:59.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't want the students to play pranks with my precious models...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.85,0:21:03.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Indeed, I can't see any antenna here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.20,0:21:04.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.70,0:21:08.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's an impressive deduction, but an unmovable object can't move.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.50,0:21:13.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It moved!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.05,0:21:17.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had Conan investigate it beforehand.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.47,0:21:24.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The antenna was replaced with an internal one, and although the engine shows evidence of having once been taken out,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.06,0:21:27.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it is currently present.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.77,0:21:31.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can you tell us why this is so?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.82,0:21:44.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It appears Shibagaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}'s objections have come to an end.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.25,0:23:19.80,Dialogue,,10,10,0,,It seems like Shibagaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} was embezzling the institute's money, and Kodama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} was asked to keep quiet in exchange for part of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.80,0:23:22.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But she got scared and broke up with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.01,0:23:26.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the school closed down, then the embezzlement would've been swept under the carpet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.60,0:23:30.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the killer really would've benefited from the murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.94,0:23:36.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Misaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s mother seems to have recovered thanks to her support.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.90,0:23:39.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And now the institute can keep going too.
